
version 3.0 (251129):
 - Switch from the non-portable and somewhat fragile schroot to a more robust solution using Docker

version 2.5 (250903):
 - Allow to install the squashfs in another directory using DISTDIR
 - Use the debian-archive-keyring package instead of relying on the deprecated apt-key
 - Actually ship the squashfs in the Debian package
 - Prebuild similarly the debian-base.tar.xz that is used Arch and other distros relying on Docker

version 2.4 (240925):
 - Ship the squashfs in the package instead of rebuilding it upon installation

version 2.3.5:
 - Fix many typos
 - Make sure that the squashfs works when it exists, or rebuild it
 - Restore the PATH and LANG envvar that got cleared in recent changes
 - Convert an input file to ascii to avoid LANG issues

version 2.3.4: Reinstall the Debian keys so that it works on Ubuntu too
version 2.3.3: Allow to use PRoot as the virtualization tool

version 2.3.2: Allow to use docker as the virtualization tool
 - Thanks to mwalp for the patch.

version 2.3.1: Use javascript to remember past answers
 - Thanks to Wyrdix for the patch.

version 2.3: Use lighttpd to serve the pages
 - This is particularly important on Ubuntu, as Firefox refuses to
   open local pages, arguing security concerns I fail to understand.
 - Add command 'shutorial list' to see what's next

version 2.2: Intial release of the v2 branch, based on schroot and squashfs 
